this is a simple logistic regression example using a predictive maintenance dataset. 
The code loads the dataset, separates features and target variable, splits the data into training and testing sets, creates a logistic regression model, trains it, makes predictions, and checks the accuracy of the model.
Make sure to read requirment.txt to see what lib you need :
python 3.14
python -m pip install sklearn 
python -m pip install pandas 
python -m pip install fsspec
Run the code in any terminal that has python in it with 
python -m {your file path}
linear regression CAN NOT BE USED ( so substitube with logistic regression)
github link https://github.com/neekonoob/lgr.py
